I"-<p>Having the proper tools makes the sourdough process easier and more reliable. You will definitely notice the difference in your final loaf.</p>

<p><strong>Starter Jar</strong></p>

<p>You will need a glass jar with a lid for your starter. The lid part is very important. I have tried using a paper towel with a rubber band but your starter gets a dry film over the top that is not ideal.</p>

<p><img src="/images/tools_jar.jpg" alt="Jar with Lid" /></p>

<p><strong>Danish Whisk</strong></p>

<p>A danish whisk isnâ€™t required but it makes mixing the dough and starter much much easier. I put off purchasing this for a year thinking it was a waster, but it is definitely worth it. You can also use a spoon/fork or silicone spatula.</p>

<p>There are two different types of whisks.</p>

<p><img src="/images/tools_whisk.jpg" alt="Danish Whisk" /></p>

